external_knowledge:
- "more recent season" refers to the most recently completed or ongoing season, in this case, '2023';
- "better-than-average active playing time" refers to the players having an average of at-bats per game higher than the league average for the 2023 season;
- "overall offensive performance" is measured by the on-base plus slugging (OPS) statistic.

; 'American League' refers to the specific division of teams within Major League Baseball;
'2022' indicates that the statistics are from the 2022 baseball season;
'batting average' is a statistical measure of a batter's performance calculated as hits divided by at bats;

sql:
SELECT 
    (SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT ps.player_id) FROM player_stats ps) AS PlayerStatsCount,
    (SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT p.team_id) FROM players p JOIN player_stats ps ON p.player_id = ps.player_id) AS TeamStatsCount;
